1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,130
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,385 --> 00:00:15,223
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:20,395
[Mercado] <i>Our person already has a lead</i>
<i>on the rooster you asked to be found.</i>

4
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:22,647
That is good news, Colonel.

5
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:24,107
[Dmitri, in English] <i>Draco</i>
<i>is my best fighter.</i>

6
00:00:24,190 --> 00:00:27,569
[Mercado] <i>He will get your Draco,</i>
<i>whatever the cost.</i>

7
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:28,737
[Martina] <i>Why did you come back here?</i>

8
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:30,280
Dad forced me.

9
00:00:30,363 --> 00:00:32,449
Are you planning to take
the company from Red?

10
00:00:32,532 --> 00:00:34,117
- Bah!
- [Karla shrieks]

11
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:34,993
[Karla] My God.

12
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:38,621
[Dmitri] <i>Master Cutter</i>
<i>is close to finding Draco.</i>

13
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:39,956
[Audrey, in English] <i>Master Cutter?</i>

14
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:43,418
[in English] He can find anything
or anyone on this earth.

15
00:00:43,501 --> 00:00:45,044
[Audrey, in English] <i>Anything?</i>

16
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:46,337
[Dmitri, in English] <i>Why?</i>

17
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,465
- <i>[Dmitri] Do you want someone found?</i>
- [in English] Maybe.

18
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:51,009
[Ibyang] Is a birthday party fun?

19
00:00:51,092 --> 00:00:53,636
[Ibyang] <i>I have not joined</i>
<i>parties like that before.</i>

20
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:54,637
[Tonet] <i>Poor you.</i>

21
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:57,515
Oh no, do not continue those thoughts.

22
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:58,892
It will only be for a moment.

23
00:00:58,975 --> 00:00:59,851
Let go of that.

24
00:00:59,934 --> 00:01:01,144
That is worth more than your life.

25
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:02,312
Just a moment.

26
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:05,774
[rooster clucks and flutters]

27
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:06,858
- [thumps]
- [grunts]

28
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,568
[Dmitri, in English]
<i>Do you have someone in mind?</i>

29
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:11,946
[Audrey, in English] <i>Yeah.</i>
<i>Someone from my past.</i>

30
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,448
[music concludes]

31
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:15,909
- Wait, hold on!
- [Tonet] Oh.

32
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:17,744
Hi, ma'am! Do you have an invitation?

33
00:01:17,827 --> 00:01:19,287
An invitation?

34
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:22,040
Yes. This birthday party
requires an invitation.

35
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:23,583
Walk-ins are not allowed.

36
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:24,834
Ah--

37
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:28,588
[tense music playing]

38
00:01:28,671 --> 00:01:33,718
- [in English] More! More! More!
- [kids exclaiming]

39
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:36,346
- [kids cheering]
- [playful music playing]

40
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:42,185
[applauding]

41
00:01:42,268 --> 00:01:44,813
- [kids] Hi!
- [Ame] What?

42
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:46,231
Did you find the rooster?

43
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:48,900
[music continues]

44
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:50,860
[rooster clucking]

45
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:52,362
[music continues]

46
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:53,947
[both chuckle]

47
00:01:54,030 --> 00:01:55,240
[Ame] Oh, come on.

48
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:56,699
- What? What am I?
- Juggling, juggling.

49
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,118
Ah, juggling, juggling.

50
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:00,370
- [feint applause]
- [sharp inhale]

51
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,374
[music continues]

52
00:02:07,544 --> 00:02:14,008
[kids cheering]

53
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:16,928
[music fades]

54
00:02:17,762 --> 00:02:19,180
[sauve music playing]

55
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:21,099
[motorcycle revving]

56
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:23,977
[sewing machine whirring]

57
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:25,562
[scratches]

58
00:02:25,645 --> 00:02:26,980
[snipping]

59
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:28,898
[sewing machine whirring]

60
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:29,691
[gun cocks]

61
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:33,486
[thumps and gunshots]

62
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:34,571
[clicking]

63
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:36,656
[snipping]

64
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:38,783
[music swells]

65
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:43,830
[music fades]

66
00:02:44,956 --> 00:02:47,500
It is your fault! Why did you do that?!

67
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:49,961
What did I do?

68
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:53,631
You ran outside!
So now, what are we going to do?

69
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:56,134
We left our things inside,
including the invitation!

70
00:02:56,217 --> 00:02:57,927
I am really dead
when your mother finds out!

71
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:01,848
If she finds out that you went outside,
she will really be angry!

72
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:04,559
She will call the police, soldiers,

73
00:03:04,642 --> 00:03:05,643
all of them!

74
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,395
- Ma'am.
- I'm here for you.

75
00:03:08,062 --> 00:03:10,440
So, sister, please. Let us go back inside.

76
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:13,735
My boss will really be angry
if he finds out my charge went out.

77
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:15,653
Please, come on.

78
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:18,781
You really are being disobedient.

79
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:20,450
Hurry. Go back inside.

80
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:23,953
[soft rock music playing]

81
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:26,205
She is right. Thank you, sis.

82
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:27,749
There, she is right.

83
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:31,336
[music fades]

84
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:34,422
[elegant classical music playing]

85
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:37,133
That is Ibyang and Tonet.
What are they doing here?

86
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:40,511
Oh no. How did Ibyang get here?

87
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:44,641
[inaudible]

88
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:52,273
Do not disturb them.

89
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,234
We are just peeking here, right?

90
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:57,528
- [Ame chuckles]
- [both tittering]

91
00:03:57,612 --> 00:04:00,698
[music fades]

92
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:04,160
Psst. Hey, Ibyang!

93
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,579
We did not agree you would eat here.

94
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:10,083
Well, we are already here, sister.

95
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,417
It would be a waste.

96
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:13,586
[bustling chatter nearby]

97
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,257
Try it. It is super delicious!

98
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:18,758
All right then.

99
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:21,052
[bustling chatter nearby]

100
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:23,596
- Delicious, right?
- [exclaims] It really is delicious!

101
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,722
Get some more.

102
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,225
[bustling chatter nearby]

103
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,520
Oh no! Why is Brother here?

104
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:31,896
[sneaky music playing]

105
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,982
Why, Sis Tonet?

106
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:35,275
Which brother?

107
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:39,737
[music swells]

108
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:48,496
[in English] And for our final act… This.

109
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:50,957
- [kids, in English] Yes!
- This ball…

110
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,835
I will turn this into a bird.

111
00:04:53,918 --> 00:04:56,087
[kids gasping and cheering]

112
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,088
[Atoy] Oh!

113
00:04:57,171 --> 00:05:02,302
- [applauding]
- [playful music playing]

114
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,304
[Atoy] Oh, oh.

115
00:05:06,347 --> 00:05:08,975
- [in English] Blow.
- [magical twinkling]

116
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:11,352
I am not fooling you.

117
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:12,812
[music swells]

118
00:05:12,895 --> 00:05:15,023
- [kids] Wow!
- [cheering]

119
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:16,899
I am turning it into a bird for you.

120
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,568
- [cheering]
- Wow!

121
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:23,489
[applause]

122
00:05:24,615 --> 00:05:27,618
[in English] Miss, excuse me.

123
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,705
Where is the opening?

124
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:31,873
There it is.

125
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:37,086
- [somber music playing]
- [mumbling]

126
00:05:40,339 --> 00:05:41,924
Wait, wait, wait.

127
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,509
[kids applauding]

128
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,303
[host] Okay, kids, did you enjoy?

129
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,555
- [kids] Yes!
- [applauding]

130
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:52,268
[host] All right, parents, you may now
get food and drinks at the back.

131
00:05:52,351 --> 00:05:53,394
[in English] Thank you!

132
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:55,855
Has it been too long,

133
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:59,442
or did he really forget me,
that is why he did not recognize me?

134
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:02,403
[Ibyang] Mmm…

135
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:05,865
What is Emerson doing here?

136
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:08,534
Everyone from Tabang Lupa
is here, invited?

137
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:13,122
[buyer] Is there no more bargaining
for Draco?

138
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:17,251
We both know that you only took
Dmitri's rooster from him.

139
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:20,505
[in English] Planning,
effort, and execution…

140
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:22,548
cost a lot of money!

141
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:26,135
Of course, I need to profit!

142
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:29,138
Maybe your hens already wore him out.

143
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:30,807
[in English] You will be the judge.

144
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:33,643
[in English] He is in prime condition.

145
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:35,394
Even if you fight him tomorrow,

146
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:37,772
your win is guaranteed!

147
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:39,565
[chuckles]

148
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:42,360
[suspicious music playing]

149
00:06:42,443 --> 00:06:43,694
[Chipper, in English]
What the hell happened?

150
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:46,155
[tense music playing]

151
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:49,492
Where is Draco?

152
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:54,413
[music continues]

153
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:57,667
Hey! Get up!

154
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,793
Why are you sleeping there?

155
00:06:58,876 --> 00:06:59,919
Where is Draco?

156
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:02,588
The magician, boss. He was here earlier.

157
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,298
He suddenly attacked me.

158
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,467
Most likely, he is the one
who took the rooster.

159
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:07,426
Useless!

160
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,053
[music continues]

161
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:11,222
- [gun cocks]
- [in English] Guys, let's go!

162
00:07:11,305 --> 00:07:15,601
- [kids] Yay!
- [exclaiming]

163
00:07:20,898 --> 00:07:22,984
[in English] Give me that! Who are you?

164
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:26,237
[in English] You are not my classmate,
and you are not my friend!

165
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,615
Why are you here at my birthday party?!

166
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:33,619
Atoy, they caught Ibyang.
What are we going to do?

167
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:36,581
[music intensifies]

168
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,553
Ah, Maya…

169
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:52,305
[music continues]

170
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:56,142
Um, they are my siblings.

171
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:57,477
Yes.

172
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,687
They do not have anyone with them
at home, so I brought them along.

173
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:02,064
Ah, I was the one who let them in here.

174
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:06,777
[clicks tongue, in English] Okay, fine.

175
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:08,821
[in English] Here is your doughnut. Sorry.

176
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,239
[music continues]

177
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,742
[in English] Guys, let us hit the piñata!

178
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:16,245
- [kids] yay!
- [exclaiming]

179
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,790
[Chipper] Stop that magician!

180
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:23,252
[tense music playing]

181
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,213
Come on, come on.

182
00:08:25,296 --> 00:08:28,549
[music continues]

183
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:29,467
Find him!

184
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,469
[music continues]

185
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,721
What?! Find him!

186
00:08:33,804 --> 00:08:35,223
You, you are an idiot!

187
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,432
Hurry!

188
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:39,852
[music intensifies]

189
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,395
[Tonet pants]

190
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:42,438
- [Tonet shrieks]
- Oh, wait, wait!

191
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:43,731
- [Tonet] Ibyang.
- Where are you going?

192
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:46,025
- [thumps]
- [man] Hey! Oh, hey!

193
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:47,401
Do not let go of me!

194
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:48,402
[screams]

195
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:50,530
[grunts and groans]

196
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:51,405
[Tonet] Whoa!

197
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:53,074
[grunting and groaning]

198
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:56,327
- [Atoy] Go, go, go, go!
- [Ame] Come on!

199
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:57,453
[Atoy] The phone! The phone!

200
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:58,746
[tense music playing]

201
00:08:58,829 --> 00:09:01,582
[Ame panting] Wait.

202
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,459
[Tonet] Ame.

203
00:09:07,046 --> 00:09:08,798
[phone rings]

204
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:09,757
Brother?

205
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,093
- [Atoy] Come on, come on, hurry, hurry.
- [Atoy on phone] <i>Karla!</i>

206
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:14,262
- We are coming out now.
- Oh, okay, okay.

207
00:09:15,137 --> 00:09:17,265
- [man] Hey, stop!
- [Ame] Oh, Ibyang!

208
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,559
[music fades]

209
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:22,478
[ominous music playing]

210
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:23,771
[car engine revving]

211
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:25,565
- [Ame shrieks]
- [Atoy] Move aside, move aside!

212
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:26,941
[grunts]

213
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:27,984
[tense music playing]

214
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,194
[Atoy] Go, go, go.

215
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:31,320
[Ame] Ibyang!

216
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:32,655
- [Atoy] Get in, get in, get in.
- Get in now, hurry!

217
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:33,614
[Atoy] Get in.

218
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:35,700
[tense music continues]

219
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:39,078
[Atoy grunts]

220
00:09:39,161 --> 00:09:40,288
[Atoy] Hold on, hold on.

221
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:43,249
[music continues]

222
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:50,548
[car engine revving]

223
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:53,175
Boss, they got away!

224
00:09:53,843 --> 00:09:55,011
Go!

225
00:09:55,094 --> 00:09:56,345
[music fades]

226
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:59,390
So until now, no one has seen
the old man who caused trouble at the bar?

227
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:01,434
What is that, a ghost?

228
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:02,893
Find him!

229
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:04,520
[phone blips]

230
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:05,521
[Red] Idiot.

231
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,649
[pensive music playing]

232
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:12,445
‪[Martina sighs]

233
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:17,908
[liquor pouring]

234
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:19,535
Do you want your head to get even hotter?

235
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:20,911
[sniffles, sighs]

236
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:24,999
What is that?

237
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:26,709
I spoke with the prodigal daughter.

238
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:31,672
[in English] It seems like Dad is going
to give her the company.

239
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:35,676
[music intensifies]

240
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:41,641
What is your read?

241
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:47,730
Does Dad already know
about the projects I am hiding?

242
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:51,942
He might be hearing things,
but nothing concrete.

243
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:53,903
[in English] Do not worry.
The main building is almost done.

244
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,863
And once Dad sees that,

245
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,615
he will see nothing wrong with you.

246
00:10:58,407 --> 00:10:59,992
[in English] He might even
be proud of you.

247
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:01,827
[music fades]

248
00:11:02,787 --> 00:11:04,205
[in English] The real problem
is your sister.

249
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:06,040
[tense music playing]

250
00:11:06,123 --> 00:11:09,418
We need to find a way
for her to return to the U.S.

251
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:15,216
[in English] No Audrey… no problem.

252
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:19,553
[music continues]

253
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:26,143
[music fades]

254
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:29,355
[gentle music playing]

255
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:32,149
This is important to me.

256
00:11:34,443 --> 00:11:36,612
[Atoy] I will come back to this.
I will come back for you.

257
00:11:36,695 --> 00:11:39,240
Tonight, I will explain everything to you.

258
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:40,866
[dramatic sting]

259
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:43,619
Did he look for me
when I suddenly disappeared?

260
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:48,457
[Dmitri] <i>Master Cutter</i>
<i>is close to finding Draco.</i>

261
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,375
[in English] <i>He is a tracker.</i>

262
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:53,921
[in English] <i>He can find anything</i>
<i>or anyone on this earth.</i>

263
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:58,634
[suspicious music playing]

264
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:06,725
Ma'am, here is the food
you asked to be cooked.

265
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:09,603
Ah, later, miss.
I will just go see Dad first.

266
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:10,604
[in English] Thank you!

267
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:13,649
We have been here for a while.

268
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:18,195
Well, because we cannot
go straight to the gate.

269
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:20,406
They are already
watching us there with security.

270
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:23,576
- Because you even brought Ibyang inside.
- [somber music playing]

271
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:25,661
We could have already left earlier.

272
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:28,164
I was the one who invited Sister Tonet.

273
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:31,917
I just wanted to eat at the birthday.

274
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:35,129
Ibyang, why did you come along here?

275
00:12:35,212 --> 00:12:39,550
Did Atoy not say he does not like
annoying and stubborn people?

276
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,385
He will be angry again with you.

277
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:44,054
Sorry.

278
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:46,807
Apologize to Sister.

279
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:48,642
[somber music playing]

280
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:49,768
Oh?

281
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:51,312
Why do your faces look so sad?

282
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:52,813
[Karla, in English] Don't worry.

283
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:55,733
Brother Atoy already foresaw
situations like this.

284
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:59,111
We will get out of here alive.

285
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,863
[brazen music playing]

286
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,072
[Atoy] Hurry, hurry, hurry, Karla!

287
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,074
[brazen music continues]

288
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,535
I am almost done here.

289
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:09,038
[Karla] I am almost there too, Brother.

290
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,331
[Atoy] Oh, go, go, go, go!

291
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:15,294
[music continues]

292
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:24,220
BAYANET
SURELY CONNECTED

293
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,140
[Atoy] Is it done?

294
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:30,309
- [Karla] This is the last one.
- [Atoy] Is it done?

295
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:33,854
[music fades]

296
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:35,689
You are all idiots!

297
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:37,942
All of you were slipped past!

298
00:13:38,025 --> 00:13:41,862
The magician's companions,
one woman and two kids!

299
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:44,448
What? Have you seen them?

300
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:46,700
Boss, all our roving guards are moving.

301
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,036
But they are all posted
at the village gate.

302
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:52,665
- Just make sure they do not get out.
- [tense music playing]

303
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:57,336
[in English] I want Draco back,
and I want that man's head!

304
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:59,588
[tense music playing]

305
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:02,258
[guard] There, the van.

306
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:04,885
It is white!

307
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:07,680
With a red sticker
is what we are watching for.

308
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:09,974
Did you not read it? Bayanet!

309
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:13,269
And it is marked for us,
The Amazing Tomtom!

310
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:16,480
[music fades]

311
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:17,523
[woman on phone] <i>Sorry, sir.</i>

312
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:20,526
<i>We do not know the magician</i>
<i>you are talking about.</i>

313
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,736
You work there, but you do not know them?

314
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:24,321
[scoffs]

315
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,657
Maybe you are an accomplice
of the thief, huh?

316
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:28,617
[in English] Let me speak to your boss!

317
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:31,370
[woman on phone]
<i>Sorry, sir. What I mean is,</i>

318
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:35,791
<i>we do not know the magician,</i>
<i>because we did not send anyone there.</i>

319
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,793
<i>Did you not cancel the booking?</i>

320
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,212
Are you making me a liar?

321
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:43,507
I was not calling to cancel the booking!

322
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:44,717
[woman on phone] <i>Wait, sir,</i>

323
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,719
<i>I have a recording of our conversation.</i>

324
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:50,472
<i>We do that in case situations</i>
<i>like this happen.</i>

325
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:53,559
- [phone bleeps]
- <i>We have a policy that if you cancel,</i>

326
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:55,603
<i>the down payment will not be refunded.</i>

327
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:57,396
[Atoy on phone, in English]
<i>That is all right.</i>

328
00:14:57,479 --> 00:15:00,524
<i>Ah, the child changed her mind.</i>

329
00:15:00,608 --> 00:15:03,402
<i>Ah, she does not want to see a magician.</i>

330
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:04,862
[phone blips]

331
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:08,449
[brazen music playing]

332
00:15:08,532 --> 00:15:14,246
- [gunshots blasting]
- [screaming]

333
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:16,749
You are unbelievable.

334
00:15:16,832 --> 00:15:18,000
Oh, boss, thank you.

335
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:20,920
[guard, in English] Sir, sir, sir!

336
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:21,837
[music fades]

337
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,297
Boss…

338
00:15:24,882 --> 00:15:25,758
What happened to your mouth?

339
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:28,010
[ominous music playing]

340
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:30,804
His mouth? Oh! We ate spaghetti.

341
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:33,098
- Brother! It is your fault!
- [mutters]

342
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:34,183
That spaghetti was intense!

343
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:35,476
Brother, you are like a child
when you eat.

344
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:37,394
The spaghetti they gave
is really delicious…

345
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:38,479
- Yes.
- Ah.

346
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:39,521
Ah, because there was spaghetti

347
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,065
being given there.

348
00:15:41,148 --> 00:15:42,066
Yes, this was from
the party earlier, brother.

349
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:44,318
- [guard] Is that so?
- Delicious, yes.

350
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:46,779
- [guard] Okay, boss.
- All right, thank you!

351
00:15:46,862 --> 00:15:47,863
- [guard] Okay.
- [Karla] Thank you!

352
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:50,950
["Tailor" playing]

353
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:54,286
♪ <i>Oh, tailor! Holding the scissors</i> ♪

354
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:56,163
Oh, come on, come on, come on.

355
00:15:56,872 --> 00:15:58,040
You take over there.

356
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:00,876
[Tonet] Go ahead.

357
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,337
[Karla] Ibyang still has so much to say.

358
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:08,634
- Sir Atoy! Sorry about that!
- [Atoy] Oh, Kurt!

359
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:11,762
I asked around where you live because…

360
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:13,347
This is just my thank you to you.

361
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:16,058
- Ahh.
- "Kuya Kurt Sarap Pares"!

362
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,102
- Wow! Wow!
- Oh, that is for you.

363
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:19,687
- This is so delicious. How is it there?
- Yes.

364
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:20,771
Is it okay now?

365
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:22,314
- No one is bothering?
- Oh, it is fine.

366
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:25,317
Well, if you really ask me,
now I have a spot here and--

367
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:28,195
Well, well, it is nearby.
You should drop by sometime.

368
00:16:28,278 --> 00:16:30,823
- Yes, we will visit.
- Yes, perfect.

369
00:16:30,906 --> 00:16:33,242
There you go! That works.
These ones eat a lot of pares.

370
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:34,702
All right. I am ready for that.

371
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:35,953
- [chuckles]
- [Atoy] Okay!

372
00:16:36,036 --> 00:16:37,037
- Thank you so much.
- Kurt, take care.

373
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:39,039
- All right, thank you.
- If there is a problem, just call.

374
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,749
Just you. All right. Thank you.

375
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:43,043
Oh, psst. Leave some for me, okay?

376
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:47,297
- Bro, watch this because, you know… Mmm.
- [phone rings]

377
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:50,968
[Atoy] Boss…

378
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:52,720
[Atoy on phone] <i>Mission accomplished.</i>

379
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:54,471
I told you I would not be embarrassed.

380
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:55,556
What do you want?

381
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:57,349
I will return this vehicle to you.
Should I bring it along?

382
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,394
Actually, I am outside now
with the client.

383
00:17:00,477 --> 00:17:01,645
Then maybe just bring it here?

384
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:03,313
[Atoy on phone, in English] <i>Okay, sir. Uh…</i>

385
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:04,898
Just text me the address.

386
00:17:04,982 --> 00:17:06,150
I will deliver it to you.

387
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,317
- Okay.
- [Atoy on phone, in English] <i>Okay, boss</i>.

388
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:09,987
[suspicious music playing]

389
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:11,488
[chuckles softly]

390
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:14,283
My man already has your rooster.

391
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,076
You will be reunited soon.

392
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:19,079
- [in English] Wow! That is very good!
- [Mercado chuckles]

393
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:20,247
‪[both chuckle]

394
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:22,124
- [in English] All right, let's go!
- [in English] Okay.

395
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:24,543
[music continues]

396
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:26,086
[chuckles grunts]

397
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:28,213
[Dmitri] This is really good news.

398
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:30,090
[chuckles]

399
00:17:30,174 --> 00:17:32,426
Oh, they are asking me
to return the rooster.

400
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:34,845
Thank you again for your help.

401
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:36,513
- Atoy.
- Yes.

402
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:41,894
I just want to ask
for forgiveness for earlier.

403
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:46,106
Let us talk about what you
and Ibyang did when I get back.

404
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:47,483
Go ahead.

405
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:49,234
Thanks again. Go on.

406
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:52,613
Ibyang, leave some for me!

407
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:54,990
- [overlapping chatter]
- Okay, okay, okay.

408
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:56,492
- Okay, thank you.
- Take care.

409
00:17:56,575 --> 00:18:00,162
[suspicious music playing]

410
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:09,296
Who are those people?

411
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,049
What are they doing at Atoy's place?

412
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:15,260
[music continues]

413
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:19,640
So, Sister Ame?

414
00:18:19,723 --> 00:18:23,811
I told you, Master is grumpy, right?

415
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:26,188
His grumpiness is understandable.

416
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:28,690
You and Tonet are at fault.

417
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:31,902
I just felt sorry for your sister.
At fault already?

418
00:18:31,985 --> 00:18:35,364
You know, I should have been
the one Atoy brought inside.

419
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:38,117
If you are jealous, just close your eyes.

420
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,660
[whimsical music playing]

421
00:18:39,743 --> 00:18:40,828
Wait a minute.

422
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,830
Maybe you intentionally
made my makeup thick, right?

423
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:44,706
That is why I have been itchy.

424
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:47,126
It is thick because you have many pores.

425
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:49,044
Of course I have pores.

426
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,255
What do you think my skin is, an onion?

427
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:53,465
No, sandpaper.

428
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:55,259
- Hey, stop it already!
- [music concludes]

429
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:57,469
Why are you fighting?

430
00:18:58,178 --> 00:18:59,721
Is it because of Brother Atoy?

431
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:01,098
- Hmm? No.
- Oh, no!

432
00:19:01,181 --> 00:19:02,683
‪[whimsical music playing]

433
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:04,685
Stay here.

434
00:19:05,769 --> 00:19:07,229
You two.

435
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:09,898
[music fades]

436
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:13,110
- Padua.
- [Atoy] Sir!

437
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:15,112
Here it is.

438
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:16,905
May I see the rooster?

439
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:18,991
- Mmm.
- Very much alive.

440
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,451
Colorful.

441
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:25,289
Well, it really is impressive.

442
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,000
I will give this to the client,

443
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:32,004
and I will just send
the balance later. Okay?

444
00:19:32,087 --> 00:19:34,131
- No problem, sir. Thank you.
- [Dmitri] Colonel!

445
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:36,884
[tense music playing]

446
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:40,053
Colonel.

447
00:19:43,056 --> 00:19:44,808
Is this Draco?

448
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:46,518
[in English] May I see?

449
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,145
[music continues]

450
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:50,647
- I will go ahead, sir.
- [in English] Hold on.

451
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:53,483
[Dmitri, in English] Is he the one?

452
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:56,320
Is this the tracker you are proud of?

453
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:57,863
[tense music playing]

454
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:00,699
[in English] I am sorry, Colonel.

455
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:03,118
I should not have followed you.

456
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,287
[Dmitri, in English]
But I could not help myself.

457
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:08,081
[in English] I want to meet
the man himself.

458
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:12,002
[in English] I am Dmitri. And you are?

459
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:13,837
[music intensifies]

460
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:15,547
[in English] I get it.

461
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:17,049
[in English] No name.

462
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:18,967
[music fades]

463
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:21,220
[in English] I will just call you
the Master Cutter.

464
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:24,431
[tense music playing]

465
00:20:37,277 --> 00:20:38,403
Guys…

466
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:42,741
Do you know the newcomers around Atoy?

467
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:46,703
You know, the new provincial assistant?

468
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:49,998
The girl who arrived
in the past few weeks.

469
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:52,167
- Ohh. Boss!
- I know her.

470
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,627
I have already seen her, right?

471
00:20:54,211 --> 00:20:56,421
What I mean is, the two kids.

472
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:58,423
Kids?

473
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:00,717
- Does Atoy have adopted children?
- Hmm?

474
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:03,595
- [groans]
- That is why I am asking you,

475
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:04,805
because I do not know!

476
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:07,599
- Well, that is on you.
- You are unbelievable.

477
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:09,059
What are you thinking?

478
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:10,644
[pensive music playing]

479
00:21:10,727 --> 00:21:12,187
I think there is…

480
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:14,564
Atoy is doing something illegal.

481
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:17,150
What kind of illegal thing is that, Boss?

482
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:19,403
- [in English] Child labor.
- [Tukmol] Oh, right.

483
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:21,238
- [Munggo] Oh…
- That is my hunch.

484
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:22,447
[Tukmol] That is serious.

485
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:23,532
[music continues]

486
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:25,242
I am sure

487
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:27,286
Atoy is hiding something.

488
00:21:28,078 --> 00:21:29,621
We need to find out.

489
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:31,707
[music fades]

490
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:34,751
Chipper Arenas?

491
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:36,545
[in English] Yes, sir.

492
00:21:36,628 --> 00:21:40,007
That bastard, that demon.

493
00:21:40,882 --> 00:21:45,304
By any chance, do you accept
special assignments?

494
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:49,641
[suspicious music playing]

495
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,689
Sorry, sir, but… [clears throat]

496
00:21:55,772 --> 00:21:58,066
I only do tracking.

497
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:02,112
[music continues]

498
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:03,322
[in English] All right.

499
00:22:03,405 --> 00:22:05,032
I will handle Chipper myself.

500
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:09,077
- [music continues]
- [phone ringing]

501
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:14,416
Excuse me. I will just answer this.

502
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,964
Yes, child?

503
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:23,842
[in English] Hey, Dad!
You are at the golf course, right?

504
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:25,218
[in English] Why are you asking?

505
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:28,680
Are you not with
that acquaintance who has…

506
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:31,308
a known contact who is a tracker?

507
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:32,684
Master Cutter.

508
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:34,728
[in English] I want to meet him.

509
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:36,688
I think he can help me.

510
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:38,690
He already left earlier.

511
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:41,693
[in English] Ah, okay. It is fine.
I will just go there anyway.

512
00:22:42,277 --> 00:22:44,154
I already left the golf course.

513
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,239
[in English] No, you did not.

514
00:22:46,948 --> 00:22:50,285
[in English] I am looking at your car
in the parking lot right now.

515
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:53,038
You are weird, Dad.

516
00:22:53,663 --> 00:22:55,040
[in English] I am on my way inside.

517
00:22:55,123 --> 00:22:59,211
[music continues]

518
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,671
[in English] I have a slight problem.

519
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:02,923
[in English] My daughter is here.

520
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:06,093
And it seems she also
wants something found.

521
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:08,095
[in English] Can you do me a favor?

522
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:10,097
What is it?

523
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:12,182
Because I told her that you already left.

524
00:23:12,265 --> 00:23:15,685
[in English] Can you just pretend you are
just normal people that I golf with?

525
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:20,440
[in English] And you are not
the Master Cutter.

526
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:25,987
You do not want what she wants found?

527
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:28,073
[in English] I am just
looking out for her.

528
00:23:28,156 --> 00:23:29,783
[in English] It is for her own good.

529
00:23:29,866 --> 00:23:34,496
[tense music playing]

530
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:39,626
Sir, maybe she is looking
for an ex-boyfriend, right?

531
00:23:40,418 --> 00:23:42,963
Or maybe a man who cheated on her.

532
00:23:43,046 --> 00:23:47,259
[music intensifies]

533
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:56,309
[in English] Dad!

534
00:23:59,146 --> 00:24:01,815
[music intensifies]

535
00:24:04,234 --> 00:24:08,738
- [electronic blipping]
- [music intensifies]

536
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:17,831
[Dmitri] <i>That man is important to Audrey.</i>

537
00:24:17,914 --> 00:24:20,750
What if we made a mistake
in what we did before?

538
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:24,462
[in English] What is important
is that we protect our secret.

539
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:26,298
[Audrey, in English] What secret?

540
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:28,466
Look, there is an issue now on FlipTok.

541
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,843
There are missing women.

542
00:24:29,926 --> 00:24:32,137
The police say they ran away.

543
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:36,016
But the families say they met someone
on a dating app and then disappeared.

544
00:24:36,099 --> 00:24:37,893
Atoy, Queenie is missing.

545
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:39,603
[Cita] <i>They need your help.</i>

546
00:24:39,686 --> 00:24:41,229
[Atoy] Where is the usual place
she hangs out?

547
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:42,772
[Rachel] I only know school and home.

548
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:44,816
<i>And at Bahay Kayakap.</i>

549
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,026
UP NEXT

550
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:50,155
[brazen music playing]
